ASSEMBLY BILL NO. 53–COMMITTEE ON EDUCATION
(ON BEHALF OF THE LIEUTENANT GOVERNOR)
PREFILED NOVEMBER 19, 2024
____________
Referred to Committee on Education
SUMMARY—Establishes provisions relating to outdoor
recreational education. (BDR 34-509)
FISCAL NOTE: Effect on Local Government: May have Fiscal Impact.
Effect on the State: Yes.
CONTAINS UNFUNDED MANDATE (§ 1)
(NOT REQUESTED BY AFFECTED LOCAL GOVERNMENT)
~
EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to education; providing for pupils in elementary
school to receive a certain amount of outdoor recess each
school day, with certain exceptions; authorizing the
approval of academic credit for outdoor recreational
activities under certain circumstances; and providing
other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law requires the board of trustees of each school district to provide
2 instruction in physical education to the pupils enrolled in the public schools within
3 the school district. (NRS 389.018) Section 1 of this bill requires the board of
4 trustees of a school district or the governing body of a charter school to adopt a
5 policy requiring at least 20 minutes of outdoor recess each school day for pupils in
6 kindergarten and grades 1 through 5. Section 1 requires the policy to include
7 provisions: (1) exempting certain pupils who are unable to participate in recess; (2)
8 prohibiting the denial of recess for reasons related to academics or behavior, except
9 in certain circumstances; and (3) requiring certain alternatives for outdoor recess
10 when weather or other conditions make outdoor recess unsafe or otherwise
11 inappropriate.
12 Section 2 of this bill authorizes the board of trustees of a school district or the
13 governing body of a charter school to authorize a pupil enrolled in junior high or
14 middle school or high school to receive academic credit for completing certain
15 approved outdoor recreational activities outside of school hours.
