THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 388 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The board of trustees of each school district shall adopt a
4 policy to require each elementary school in the school district to
5 provide recess each school day to pupils in kindergarten and
6 grades 1 to 5, inclusive.
7 2. The governing body of each charter school that provides
8 instruction to pupils in kindergarten or grade 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5 shall
9 adopt a policy to require each such school to provide recess each
10 school day to each such pupil.
11 3. The policy adopted pursuant to subsection 1 or 2 must
12 include, without limitation:
13 (a) A requirement that each elementary school within the
14 school district or the charter school, as applicable, provide at least
15 20 minutes of outdoor recess each school day to each pupil in
16 kindergarten or grade 1, 2, 3, 4 or 5;
17 (b) A provision for an exemption if a pupil is unable to
18 participate in recess because of an illness or a disability or is
19 otherwise physically unable to participate in recess;
20 (c) A provision prohibiting a teacher, an administrator or any
21 other person from denying a pupil the outdoor recess required
22 pursuant to paragraph (a) for reasons relating to behavior or
23 academics, except when:
24 (1) An academic goal cannot reasonably be achieved
25 through other means; or
26 (2) The safety or welfare of the pupil or other persons
27 cannot reasonably be protected through other means; and
28 (d) A provision for substituting appropriate indoor activities
29 for the outdoor recess required pursuant to paragraph (a) in the
30 event that weather or other conditions make outdoor recess unsafe
31 or otherwise inappropriate.
32 Sec. 2. Chapter 389 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
33 thereto a new section to read as follows:
34 1. The board of trustees of a school district or the governing
35 body of a charter school may authorize a pupil enrolled in a junior
36 high or middle school or a high school who completes an outdoor
37 recreational activity that is approved pursuant to subsection 2 to
38 receive credit toward the total number of credits required for
39 promotion to high school or graduation from high school, as
40 applicable. Any credit earned for completing an outdoor
41 recreational activity pursuant to this section must be applied
42 towards the pupil’s elective course credit.
