1 2. The board of trustees of a school district or the governing
2 body of a charter school may approve for credit pursuant to
3 subsection 1 an outdoor recreational activity that:
4 (a) Is completed outside of school hours;
5 (b) Requires a pupil to spend a significant amount of time
6 outdoors; and
7 (c) Teaches the pupil skills that are relevant to outdoor
8 education which may include, without limitation:
9 (1) Identifying plants and animals native to this State;
10 (2) Building trails;
11 (3) Restoring natural habitats;
12 (4) Outdoor survival skills;
13 (5) Outdoor sportsmanship skills, including, without
14 limitation, hiking and archery; and
15 (6) Bird watching.
16 3. If the board of trustees of a school district or the governing
17 body of a charter school approves outdoor recreational activities
18 for credit pursuant to subsection 1, the board of trustees or
19 governing body, as applicable, shall prescribe the:
20 (a) Maximum amount of total credits that a pupil may earn for
21 completing outdoor recreational activities;
22 (b) Rules regarding how a pupil may apply for such credit
23 upon the completion of an approved outdoor recreational activity;
24 and
25 (c) Procedures for obtaining the consent of a parent or legal
26 guardian of a pupil before the pupil may participate in an outdoor
27 recreational activity for which credit will be granted.
28 4. This section shall not be construed to require the board of
29 trustees of a school district or the governing body of a charter
30 school to provide, facilitate or spend money to provide, facilitate or
31 sponsor any outdoor recreational activity.
32 Sec. 3. The provisions of NRS 354.599 do not apply to any
33 additional expenses of a local government that are related to this act.
34 Sec. 4. 1. This section becomes effective upon passage and
35 approval.
36 2. Sections 1, 2 and 3 of this act become effective:
37 (a) Upon passage and approval for the purpose of adopting any
38 regulations and performing any other preparatory administrative
39 tasks that are necessary to carry out the provisions of this act; and
40 (b) On July 1, 2025, for all other purposes.
